[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 9. Loading, Closing, and Active State

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
History loading reconstructs stable bodies, overlays current metadata, and re-synchronizes SQLite.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-ID
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: History Lookup by file_id
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryManager.load_history shall resolve the requested history through memory_files.file_id and shall fail when no matching row exists.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-FIELDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Loaded File-Level State
STATEMENT: >>>
Loading shall set file_id, title, filename_ragmem, and filename_meta from the SQLite file row.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-ID

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-RECORDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Loaded Record State
STATEMENT: >>>
Loading shall replace the current record list with MemoryRecords read from the selected .ragmem file.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-ID

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-PENDING-RESET
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Pending Buffer Reset on Load
STATEMENT: >>>
Loading a history shall reset pending_activebrief_topic_buffer to empty.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-ID

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-CREATED-FLAG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Loaded File-Created Flag
STATEMENT: >>>
After load, b_file_created shall indicate whether the selected .ragmem path exists.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-ID

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-REFRESH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SQLite Refresh after Load
STATEMENT: >>>
After loading bodies and metadata, MemoryManager shall refresh the SQLite mirror for the active history.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-LOAD-ID

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-CLOSE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: MemoryManager Close
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryManager.close shall save current metainfo and refresh the SQLite index.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 10. Memory History File Operations

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryFileManager owns explicit file-level operations while delegating active record semantics to MemoryManager.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-LIST
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: List Histories
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryFileManager.list_histories shall return the MemoryManager SQLite history listing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-CREATE-TITLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Create History Title Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryFileManager.create_history shall reject an empty title.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-CREATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Create Empty History
STATEMENT: >>>
Creating an empty history shall make it active, create an empty .ragmem file, create paired .ragmeta.json content, and create or update the memory_files row with record_count zero.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-CREATE-TITLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-CREATE-TIMES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Empty History Timestamps
STATEMENT: >>>
An explicitly created empty history shall use current UTC for both created_at_utc and updated_at_utc in its initial metadata.
