RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-CREATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-LOAD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: File Manager Load
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryFileManager.load_history shall validate file_id and delegate active-history loading to MemoryManager.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-TITLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rename Title Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryFileManager.rename_history shall reject an empty file_id or new title and shall reject unknown file_id values.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-ID
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rename Preserves file_id
STATEMENT: >>>
Renaming a memory history shall preserve file_id.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-TITLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-PAIR
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rename Paired Files
STATEMENT: >>>
Renaming shall rename the physical .ragmem and .ragmeta.json files when they exist and update their stored filename fields.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-TITLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-TIMESTAMP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rename Timestamp Prefix
STATEMENT: >>>
Renaming shall preserve an existing YYYY-MM-DD-HH-MM filename prefix when present; otherwise it shall use the current minute prefix.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-TITLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-COLLISION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rename Collision Handling
STATEMENT: >>>
When either target filename already exists, rename shall append the first eight characters of file_id to the new stem.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-TITLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-SQLITE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rename SQLite Update
STATEMENT: >>>
Renaming shall update title, paired filenames, and updated_at_utc in memory_files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-TITLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-ACTIVE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rename Active History
STATEMENT: >>>
When the renamed history is active, MemoryManager file-level state shall be updated and its metadata and SQLite mirror shall be refreshed.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-TITLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-INACTIVE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rename Inactive History
STATEMENT: >>>
When the renamed history is not active, the renamed metadata file shall have its file-level title, paired filenames, and updated timestamp updated without loading the history.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-RENAME-TITLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-DELETE-VALIDATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Delete History Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryFileManager.delete_history shall reject an empty or unknown file_id.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-DELETE-VECTORS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Delete History Vectors
STATEMENT: >>>
When a compatible MemoryVectorStore is supplied, deleting a history shall request deletion of vectors by file_id before deleting SQLite rows and files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-DELETE-VALIDATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-DELETE-SQLITE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Delete History SQLite Rows
STATEMENT: >>>
Deleting a history shall remove matching rows from memory_records and memory_files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-DELETE-VALIDATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-DELETE-PHYSICAL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Delete History Physical Files
STATEMENT: >>>
Deleting a history shall unlink its .ragmem and .ragmeta.json files when present.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-DELETE-VALIDATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-REC-FILE-DELETE-ACTIVE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Delete Active History State
STATEMENT: >>>
When the deleted history is active, the current implementation shall replace file_id, clear title and filenames, clear records and metainfo, and mark b_file_created false.
